---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { getAllListings, getPublishedMetros } from '../../lib/listings';
import { breadcrumbJsonLd } from '../../lib/seo';

const listings = getAllListings();
const metros = getPublishedMetros();
// Real pipeline funnel: raw Maps businesses ingested across all target
// cities (pipeline DB, sessions 4-18) vs. the ones that actually publish
// verifiable pricing. The pass rate IS the proof the verification is real —
// update this alongside listings.json when new metros are ingested.
const rawBusinessesChecked = 1057;

const title = 'About & Methodology | EventRentalCosts.com';
const description = 'How we collect and verify real party and event rental pricing data — no fabricated numbers, no fake reviews.';
const breadcrumbs = [
  { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
  { label: 'About & Methodology', href: '/about/' },
];
const jsonLd = [breadcrumbJsonLd(breadcrumbs)];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} path="/about/" jsonLd={jsonLd}>
  <div class="container narrow">
    <Breadcrumbs items={breadcrumbs} />
    <h1>About &amp; Methodology</h1>

    <p>
      EventRentalCosts.com is an independent comparison site for party and event equipment
      rental pricing across {metros.length} US metro areas — currently
      {' '}{metros.map((m) => m.meta.name).join(', ')}. We are not affiliated with, and don't
      receive payment from, any company listed here as of this writing.
    </p>

    <h2>How we find companies</h2>
    <p>
      We identify real party, tent, table, and chair rental businesses using Google Maps data —
      name, address, phone, rating, and review count. We manually filter out businesses that
      Google's broad category matching pulls in by accident (venues, DJs, caterers, retail
      stores) and only include businesses actually in the equipment rental business.
    </p>

    <h2>How we collect pricing</h2>
    <p>
      For each business, we scrape their own website directly — never a third-party directory
      or marketplace — looking for a real, published dollar figure. We do not estimate, average,
      or guess at pricing. The bar is high on purpose: of the roughly {rawBusinessesChecked.toLocaleString()} rental-category
      businesses we've checked across our metro areas, only {listings.length} publish real,
      verifiable pricing on their own websites — and those are the only ones listed here. The
      rest require a phone call or quote request, so we don't list pricing for them (we'd rather
      list nothing than a fabricated number). Every extracted price is also automatically
      re-checked against the exact sentence it came from before it's published.
    </p>

    <h2>What "not published" means</h2>
    <p>
      For details like delivery availability, setup service, or weekend surcharges, we only mark
      "Yes" or "No" when a business explicitly states it on their website. If a business doesn't
      mention something at all, we mark it "Not published" — we never assume a missing detail
      means "no." That distinction matters: silence isn't the same as a real answer.
    </p>

    <h2>How current is this data?</h2>
    <p>
      Each listing shows the date its pricing was last checked. Rental pricing can change,
      especially seasonally, so always confirm current pricing directly with the business before
      booking.
    </p>

    <h2>How this site makes money</h2>
    <p>
      We plan to earn through referral relationships with listed businesses and, once traffic
      justifies it, display advertising. As of this writing we have no paid placements — company
      order in comparison tables is based on price, not payment.
    </p>

    <h2>Found an error?</h2>
    <p>
      If pricing on this site is wrong or a business wants a correction, email
      {' '}<a href="mailto:contact@eventrentalcosts.com">contact@eventrentalcosts.com</a> and
      we'll fix it — real accuracy is the entire point of this site.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .narrow { max-width: 720px; }
  h2 { margin-top: var(--space-8); }
</style>
